onal lines above and below: “FIRST IN BLACK AND WHITE TELEVISION” and “FIRST IN COMPATIBLE COLOR TELEVISION.” At the lower left is an RCA circle logo. To the right, the RCA Victor dog mascot sits beside an old-fashioned gramophone horn, listening toward it. Beneath the dog and gramophone appears the phrase “HIS MASTER’S VOICE.”",
